50|$|This {{class were}} {{compound}} Mallet locomotives: {{as well as}} being articulated between the forward, swinging engine unit and the rear fixed one, they were <b>compound</b> <b>locomotives.</b> The rear, high-pressure cylinders exhausted their steam into the huge front cylinders. Like many <b>compound</b> <b>locomotives,</b> they could be operated in simple mode for starting; reduced-pressure steam could be sent straight from the boiler to the front cylinders at low speed, for maximum tractive effort.|$|R
